#. <section class="sutta" id="an6.11"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an6.11:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 6"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 6"

#. </p><p>
#. VAR: 2. Sāraṇīyavagga → sārāṇiyādivaggo (s1-3)
msgctxt "an6.11:0.2"
msgid "2. Sāraṇīyavagga"
msgstr "2. Warm-hearted"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an6.11:0.3"
msgid "11. Paṭhamasāraṇīyasutta"
msgstr "11. Warm-hearted (1st)"

# For sāraṇīya, see BB’s note. Also see Ghd dict: saṃrajadi (Skt. saṃrajyate) v. is pleased.
#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. VAR: sāraṇīyā → sārāṇīyā (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an6.11:1.1"
msgid "“Chayime, bhikkhave, dhammā sāraṇīyā."
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these six warm-hearted qualities."

msgctxt "an6.11:1.2"
msgid "Katame cha?"
msgstr "What six?"

msgctxt "an6.11:1.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno mettaṃ kāyakammaṃ paccupaṭṭhitaṃ hoti "
"sabrahmacārīsu āvi ceva raho ca, ayampi dhammo sāraṇīyo. (1)"
msgstr ""
"Firstly, a mendicant consistently treats their spiritual companions with "
"bodily kindness, both in public and in private. This is a warm-hearted "
"quality."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an6.11:2.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno mettaṃ vacīkammaṃ paccupaṭṭhitaṃ hoti "
"sabrahmacārīsu āvi ceva raho ca, ayampi dhammo sāraṇīyo. (2)"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant consistently treats their spiritual companions with "
"verbal kindness, both in public and in private. This too is a warm-hearted "
"quality."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an6.11:3.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno mettaṃ manokammaṃ paccupaṭṭhitaṃ hoti "
"sabrahmacārīsu āvi ceva raho ca, ayampi dhammo sāraṇīyo. (3)"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant consistently treats their spiritual companions with "
"mental kindness …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.289"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an6.11:4.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ye te lābhā dhammikā dhammaladdhā antamaso "
"pattapariyāpannamattampi tathārūpehi lābhehi appaṭivibhattabhogī hoti "
"sīlavantehi sabrahmacārīhi sādhāraṇabhogī, ayampi dhammo sāraṇīyo. (4)"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant shares without reservation any material possessions "
"they have gained by legitimate means, even the food placed in the alms-bowl, "
"using them in common with their ethical spiritual companions. This too is a "
"warm-hearted quality."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an6.11:5.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu yāni tāni sīlāni akhaṇḍāni acchiddāni "
"asabalāni akammāsāni bhujissāni viññuppasatthāni aparāmaṭṭhāni "
"samādhisaṃvattanikāni tathārūpehi sīlehi sīlasāmaññagato viharati "
"sabrahmacārīhi āvi ceva raho ca, ayampi dhammo sāraṇīyo. (5)"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant lives according to the precepts shared with their "
"spiritual companions, both in public and in private. Those precepts are "
"uncorrupted, unflawed, unblemished, untainted, liberating, praised by "
"sensible people, not mistaken, and leading to immersion. This too is a warm-"
"hearted quality."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an6.11:6.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu yāyaṃ diṭṭhi ariyā niyyānikā niyyāti "
"takkarassa sammā dukkhakkhayāya tathārūpāya diṭṭhiyā diṭṭhisāmaññagato "
"viharati sabrahmacārīhi āvi ceva raho ca, ayampi dhammo sāraṇīyo. (6)"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant lives according to the view shared with their "
"spiritual companions, both in public and in private. That view is noble and "
"emancipating, and leads one who practices it to the complete ending of "
"suffering. This too is a warm-hearted quality."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an6.11:7.1"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, cha dhammā sāraṇīyā”ti."
msgstr "These are the six warm-hearted qualities.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an6.11:7.2"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
